trailingComments.value: Since vue-router v3.1, a new promise-based API is in effect for programmatic navigation methods. Our existing code
is not aware of it yet, which leads to console errors in case a promise is rejected since it's never caught.
Note that this occurs even in expected situations (NavigationDuplicated), which are not considered errors.
FIXME: Here we introduce a compatibility layer, where we overload the original methods and make them behave exactly
like the old ones, but while catching any rejected promises and exceptions.
Original methods are still preserved, but under new *Async() names.
